-- ADP: U.S. Firms Added 13K Workers in June, Trailing Estimates
-- Shobhana Chandra
-- 2010-06-30T12:17:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/u-s-companies-added-13-000-workers-in-june-less-than-estimated-adp-says.html

          
          
             Companies in the U.S. expanded
payrolls by 13,000 in June, according to figures from ADP
Employer Services.  
 The ADP figures were forecast to show a gain of 60,000
jobs, according to the median estimate of 36 economists surveyed
by Bloomberg. Projections ranged from 23,000 to 100,000.  
 To contact the reporters on this story:
 Shobhana Chandra  in Washington at 
 schandra1@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
                     The lack of jobs will curtail consumer spending, slowing down U.S economic recovery. Photographer: Ronda Churchill/Bloomberg  
                           

     
